Put all your custom variables in the brackets

​@Advaiya Lad  
First , create a file and import only things you need, not entire library 
Let's say vendor/bootstrap.scss
```
// Configuration
@import "boostrap/scss/functions";
@import "boostrap/scss/variables";
@import "boostrap/scss/mixins";
@import "boostrap/scss/utilities";

// Layout & components
@import "boostrap/scss/navbar";
...
```

Then your main scss file should be something like this 

```
@use "vendor/bootstrap" as bs5 with (
   $grays: (...),
   $grid-breakpoints: ( pc: ..., sp: ..., tablet: .. ),
   $theme-colors: ( primary: ..., accept: ... , refuse: ...)
);

// When you want to use bs media-query
@include bs5.media-breakpoint-up(pc) {
   .navbar { ... }
 }
```
With this you can custom not only value but even class name
it will automatically create customized utilities class, mixin for you too, like col-pc, col-sp, or btn-accept ..
And all other thing you don't need will be removed , like col-xs col-sm...
I think this is the right way to use bootstrap or other library with customize
